news.title: Lucknow development body sold properties worth Rs 2,629 crore in FY24
news.para: LDA vice-chairman Indramani Tripathi attributed this success to the e-auction initiative. Commercial and residential properties valued at Rs 2,058.64 crore were successfully auctioned online.

news.title: Rajkot civic body collects property tax worth Rs 365.49 crore in FY24
news.para: This has made the tax income of RMC rise by more than 90% over the last five financial years — from Rs 189.58 crore in 2019-20 to Rs 365.49 crore in 2023-24.

news.title: Pimpri Chinchwad civic body collects property tax worth Rs 977 crore in FY24
news.para: Civic officials said the municipal corporation earned Rs977 crore revenue through property tax this fiscal, compared to Rs810 crore collected in 2022-23 and Rs628 crore in 2021-22.

news.title: Halted drive in merged areas hits Pune civic body's property tax earnings in FY24
news.para: Property tax is usually the largest source of revenue for Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC). Around Rs2,268 crore was earned from it in the latest fiscal, states official data.

news.title: Lucknow civic body collects property tax worth over Rs 650 crore in FY24
news.para: The achievement was driven by a remarkable increase of over 26% in property and house tax collection, soaring from Rs 338 crore to Rs 425 crore compared to the previous fiscal year.

news.title: Lucknow civic body launches campaign to update KYC record
news.para: The LMC employeeswill update the mobile numbers and other missing records of the property owners. This will help the corporation to coordinate with customers and provide various details of schemes, taxes, and other information by the LMC.

news.title: With 10% hike in circle rates, land prices in Jaipur escalates
news.para: At present, the highest district level committee (DLC) rate in Jaipur is for C-Scheme and MI Road areas, where per square feet costs range between Rs 90,000 and Rs 1.25 lakh.

news.title: Maharashtra's IGR department earns Rs 50,143 crore in FY24
news.para: The registration of property with inspector general of registration (IGR) department was a key contributor to the state exchequer.

news.title: Apartments in Bengaluru not finding tankers to sell treated water
news.para: Bengaluru apartments sell treated water, facing tanker shortage. Rajagopalan R sells from 5 blocks daily. Tankers can't supply drinking water. BAF vice-president struggles. Credai partnership for treated water revenue with BWSSB supply starting soon.

news.title: Guruguram civic body falls 50% short of revenue target from property tax in FY24
news.para: “Residential, institutional, commercial and industrial properties in the city have to pay property tax as per the Haryana Municipal Corporation Act, 1994.

news.title: Secure sites, share Mahira Homes' financial information: Buyers to Haryana RERA
news.para: Two weeks back, regulator had revoked all the five affordable housing projects of the developer as it failed to comply with the provisions of Rera Act and complete the projects.

news.title: SWAMIH Fund invests Rs 300 crore in Hubtown's project in Mumbai
news.para: SWAMIH I invested in Hubtown's Rising City project near Eastern Express Highway, benefiting homebuyers amidst regulatory issues, as part of the government's initiative to aid stalled projects.

news.title: Delhi civic body extends last date or geo-tagging properties till June 30
news.para: If a taxpayer fails to geo-tag their property, they cannot avail the rebate on the lumpsum payment of tax by June 30 in the current financial year 2024-25, the notification added.

news.title: NCLAT rejects homebuyers' plea for insolvency against Ansal Hi-tech Township
news.para: The National Company Law Appellate Tribunal (NCLAT) on Monday set aside a plea seeking insolvency proceedings against Ansal Hi-tech Township Ltd filed by its homebuyers of a project in Greater Noida.

news.title: Greece lifts price of Golden Visa to fight housing crisis
news.para: Greece on Sunday tightened its Golden Visa rules raising the required investment to as much as 800,000 euros in a bid to help ease a housing crisis.

news.title: New home prices in China rise by 0.27% in March 2024
news.para: The average new home price across 100 cities rose 0.27% on month in March, the biggest rise since July 2021, showed data from real estate researcher China Index Academy. That compared with a 0.14% on-month gain in February.

news.title: Chandigarh housing board directors fail to meet for 10 months
news.para: Hitesh Puri, chairman, Crawfed, said, “The committee was set up last year after directions from the UT administrator to officials to re-examine the issue of need-based changes. It also made recommendations to the effect and the board has to take a call on these.

news.title: No takers for over 6,800 flats build for EWS in Chennai's Ennore
news.para: 6,877 EWS flats in Ennore remain unoccupied due to poor air quality. TNHB handed the complex to TNUHDB for allotment to evicted residents. Concerns raised by TNPCB, activists, and residents have led to future stricter rules.

news.title: Pune civic body to demolish 46 dilapidated wadas before monsoon
news.para: PMC plans to demolish 46 dilapidated wadas in prime city locations like Ganesh Peth, Ghorpade Peth, and Mangalwar Peth. Seeking police intervention due to tenant opposition and fear of losing rights.
